### [3 Kings (1 Kings) Chapter 11](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#001.md)

[3 Kings (1 Kings)](../../../bib/kjv/kg1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">kg1 11:0</span></span>

Overview

[Kg1 11:1](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#001.md), Solomon's wives and
concubines; [Kg1 11:4](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#004.md), In his old age
they draw him to idolatry; [Kg1 11:9](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#009.md),
God threatens him; [Kg1 11:14](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#014.md),
Solomon's adversaries were Hadad, who was entertained in Egypt; [Kg1
11:23](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#023.md), Rezon, who reigned in Damascus;
[Kg1 11:26](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#026.md), and Jeroboam, to whom
Ahijah prophesied; [Kg1 11:41](../../../bib/kjv/kg1011.htm#041.md),
Solomon's acts, reign, and death. Rehoboam succeeds him.

